President Obama called Governor John Hickenlooper to receive an update on the fires in Colorado, including the Black Forest fire. The President expressed condolences for those who lost loved ones and concern about the extensive damage. He thanked the firefighters and pledged continued support from the federal government. Over 1,000 personnel are responding to the fires, and FEMA has approved Fire Management Assistance Grants. The Department of Defense will provide resources for suppression efforts. The President asked the Governor to inform him of any additional resources needed.